This paper deals with the analysis of error probabilities in polar codes, which are a type of error-correcting code used in information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves the study of channel coding, which falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.SI (Systems and Control). The development of transformations on synthetic channels involves the use of algorithms and data structures, which are relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the study of error probabilities in communication systems is relevant to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
